20:42.241 --> 20:44.852
I'm filled with love for you,
sons, my sons.

20:44.895 --> 20:50.684
Chock-full, brim, then spilling,
sons, with love for you.

20:52.251 --> 20:54.296
Let me tell you our story.

20:55.602 --> 20:59.127
What else can you
tell me about Paul?

21:01.303 --> 21:03.392
Certified muff diver.

21:03.436 --> 21:05.438
How's that? Wh-- Muff?

21:05.481 --> 21:06.874
[ Clears throat ]

21:06.917 --> 21:10.878
My sister, Lillian --
she had an innocent...

21:12.706 --> 21:15.665
She bought Paul
a shirt here --

21:15.709 --> 21:19.103
"Certified muff diver."

21:19.147 --> 21:22.324
She didn't realize, you know,
what it meant --

21:22.368 --> 21:24.370
the sexual aspect of it.

21:24.413 --> 21:27.329
She just thought it meant,

21:27.373 --> 21:32.378
uh..."reef"
or something oceanic.

21:32.421 --> 21:34.162
I don't know.

21:34.205 --> 21:37.426
Anyway, after that,

21:37.470 --> 21:41.212
he used to wear it...
from time to time...

21:41.256 --> 21:43.824
make her laugh.

21:43.867 --> 21:47.741
So now I look at this photo
from time to time

21:47.784 --> 21:49.569
to make me laugh.

21:49.612 --> 21:50.874
Paul Brown?

21:50.918 --> 21:52.223
Yeah.

21:52.267 --> 21:59.187
♪♪

21:59.230 --> 22:02.930
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

22:02.973 --> 22:05.236
I'm sorry.
It's my daughter.

22:06.629 --> 22:08.849
Hi, honey,
call me a little later.

22:08.892 --> 22:11.373
[ Sighs ]

22:13.810 --> 22:16.291
Are you sure you gave
the right one back?

22:16.335 --> 22:18.075
Yeah, man.

22:18.119 --> 22:20.208
'Cause I don't want you
trying to kill me

22:20.251 --> 22:23.124
every time someone's table's
ready in a Mexican Chili's.

22:23.167 --> 22:24.647
Yeah.

22:24.691 --> 22:28.738
The one I gave back to the gal
was still buzzing.

22:30.392 --> 22:32.655
Left isn't west.

22:33.917 --> 22:35.615
What?

22:35.658 --> 22:38.313
Sometimes it is,
I mean, but...

22:38.357 --> 22:40.228
sometimes it isn't.

22:40.271 --> 22:42.056
Life taught me that.

22:44.232 --> 22:46.539
-Cool.
-Thanks.

22:49.759 --> 22:51.761
How's your head?

22:53.110 --> 22:54.764
I still feel pain,

22:54.808 --> 23:00.074
but I also feel pride next to
the pain, like roommates.

23:02.032 --> 23:03.686
Well, that's good,
Glenn.

23:03.730 --> 23:05.253
Yeah.

23:05.296 --> 23:08.212
Sounds like life.

23:08.256 --> 23:11.085
I'm not gonna put
my gear back on again.

23:13.043 --> 23:15.568
I'm gonna take
the pain of life.

23:18.745 --> 23:20.573
Hey.

23:22.270 --> 23:24.098
Special Boys.

23:25.752 --> 23:27.449
Special Boys.

23:27.493 --> 23:29.103
[ Glasses clink ]

23:34.891 --> 23:37.198
What do we do again?

23:37.241 --> 23:38.895
What do we do what?

23:39.940 --> 23:41.811
Our gang.

23:41.855 --> 23:45.336
Do we do good deeds?

23:47.948 --> 23:50.559
No.

23:50.603 --> 23:53.214
Do we spread awareness?

23:55.521 --> 23:57.000
Not really.

23:59.873 --> 24:02.223
What do we do?

24:03.746 --> 24:07.620
We just go around...

24:07.663 --> 24:10.274
supporting each other.

24:10.318 --> 24:13.234
Go around what?

24:15.149 --> 24:16.542
We just go...

24:16.585 --> 24:20.676
like, if you're in a place

24:20.720 --> 24:24.332
and you just got a haircut,

24:24.375 --> 24:28.771
we notice that shit
and we say,

24:28.815 --> 24:32.558
"Hey, man...nice haircut."

24:32.601 --> 24:34.647
Cool.

24:34.690 --> 24:36.779
And if it's not
a good haircut

24:36.823 --> 24:40.566
and we're in a place,
we say, uh...

24:40.609 --> 24:43.003
"Hey, man,
it'll grow out."

24:43.046 --> 24:44.831
It always grows out.

24:44.874 --> 24:46.528
Always grows out.

24:46.572 --> 24:48.748
[ Glasses clink ]

24:54.362 --> 24:56.886
How many Special Boys
are there?

24:58.409 --> 25:01.238
Um...

25:01.282 --> 25:03.371
three.

25:04.981 --> 25:06.809
For now.

25:06.853 --> 25:09.943
For now,
but that, like...

25:09.986 --> 25:13.033
That makes it
more special.

25:16.210 --> 25:19.387
Yeah, it does...
make it more special.

25:27.874 --> 25:30.616
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

25:35.969 --> 25:37.753
Excuse me.

25:37.797 --> 25:40.321
I think your friend
left this at the table.

25:42.497 --> 25:44.281
Thank you.

25:44.325 --> 25:45.935
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

25:45.979 --> 25:47.284
Hey.

25:47.328 --> 25:49.548
Oh, thank you, sweetheart.

25:50.766 --> 25:52.942
No, I haven't been home yet.

25:52.986 --> 25:58.513
♪♪

25:58.557 --> 26:04.867
♪♪

26:04.911 --> 26:07.609
[ Beeps ]

26:07.653 --> 26:09.742
Man: Attention. We have
an emergency bulletin

26:09.785 --> 26:11.657
from The Kilroy County
Sheriff's Service...

26:11.700 --> 26:13.789
One hears, doesn't one,

26:13.833 --> 26:17.663
about the God-shaped hole
in human hearts?

26:17.706 --> 26:20.143
Which expresses, my guess,

26:20.187 --> 26:22.624
the hunger for splendor,
for grace,

26:22.668 --> 26:24.887
for big love, for mercy,

26:24.931 --> 26:27.194
for tenderness, more big love,
and peace.

26:27.237 --> 26:29.152
And there isa hole.

26:29.196 --> 26:31.198
Fuck, yes. Pardon.

26:31.241 --> 26:34.505
There's a hole...
in all our hearts.

26:34.549 --> 26:37.813
But they got the shape wrong.

26:37.857 --> 26:40.555
It's dad-shaped, lads.

26:40.599 --> 26:44.864
So many of us endeavor,
strive,

26:44.907 --> 26:47.997
so many of us struggle
here together

26:48.041 --> 26:51.131
with the father-shaped
empty space

26:51.174 --> 26:55.962
in our lives where good old Dad
should be, but rarely is.

26:56.005 --> 26:58.442
Absent, alcoholic,

26:58.486 --> 26:59.879
distracted, put upon,

26:59.922 --> 27:02.664
limited, ornery, impatient,

27:02.708 --> 27:05.928
bigoted, plain fucking --
pardon -- stupid.

27:05.972 --> 27:08.583
These are our fathers,
children...

27:08.627 --> 27:10.106
if you have fathers at all.

27:10.150 --> 27:11.455
Many of you do not.

27:11.499 --> 27:13.066
And none of you, I imagine,

27:13.109 --> 27:16.852
have good old Dad
except these two.

27:16.896 --> 27:18.637
No.

27:21.552 --> 27:23.380
Hello, boys.

27:24.643 --> 27:26.557
I'm good old Dad.

27:26.601 --> 27:31.171
♪♪

27:31.214 --> 27:34.957
Paul Allen Brown's
gone again, Judge...

27:35.001 --> 27:39.092
simultaneous to the half-day
that a child has gone missing,

27:39.135 --> 27:41.660
simultaneous
almost to the hour.

27:43.270 --> 27:44.314
Judge.

27:44.358 --> 27:46.534
Judge: Yeah, Wesley?

27:46.577 --> 27:49.102
It feels the same.

27:49.145 --> 27:51.800
Wesley, I can't give you an
arrest warrant based on that.

27:51.844 --> 27:53.149
It's not enough.

27:53.193 --> 27:55.456
Goodbye, Wesley.

27:57.023 --> 27:59.678
[ Thunder rumbles,
rain falling ]

28:02.463 --> 28:05.466
Woman: Byron!

28:05.509 --> 28:10.732
I met the boys' mother
at an airport bar in Honduras.

28:10.776 --> 28:12.734
Travelers --

28:12.778 --> 28:14.780
she, bound for Mexico,

28:14.823 --> 28:16.912
I, elsewhere,

28:16.956 --> 28:19.306
thrust together.

28:19.349 --> 28:20.568
Connection.

28:20.611 --> 28:22.396
Oh, how we laughed.

28:22.439 --> 28:25.051
The small things drew us
together.

28:25.094 --> 28:27.618
Walking together,
talking at times,

28:27.662 --> 28:29.838
not talking at times, being,

28:29.882 --> 28:34.582
just being...being as one...

28:34.625 --> 28:39.805
until it was taken hostage
by forces...

28:39.848 --> 28:43.112
held as a hostage,

28:43.156 --> 28:46.855
presumed dead by your mother,
my darling,

28:46.899 --> 28:49.945
sparing you, my boys,
the horror.

28:49.989 --> 28:52.469
Secret father.

28:52.513 --> 28:56.125
Escape...my every thought.
Reach the boys.

28:56.169 --> 28:59.302
I...devised and...

28:59.346 --> 29:02.262
executed
my escape this past Tuesday,

29:02.305 --> 29:06.483
journeyed immediately to you,
secret sons.

29:06.527 --> 29:09.530
Those, um [Clears throat]
ice-cream moments --

29:09.573 --> 29:15.405
those moments were my effort to
ease into the remarkable yous.

29:15.449 --> 29:18.931
Rented an ice-cream rig.

29:18.974 --> 29:20.541
Went the extra mile.

29:20.584 --> 29:24.371
Missed the chance to deliver
the big news.

29:24.414 --> 29:27.069
Ice-cream-wise.
Here now.

29:27.113 --> 29:29.289
Diving in...

29:29.332 --> 29:31.508
into the remarkable news.

29:31.552 --> 29:32.771
How did you escape?

29:32.814 --> 29:33.772
Karate.

29:33.815 --> 29:35.077
Did you kill anyone?

29:35.121 --> 29:37.210
Everyone --
Everyone that held me

29:37.253 --> 29:39.473
and kept me
from my secret sons.

29:40.735 --> 29:45.609
Wesley: Sheriff, Paul Brown --
Paul Allen Brown, my guy...

29:45.653 --> 29:46.915
Sheriff: Yeah?

29:46.959 --> 29:49.309
...my guy
with the girl thing?

29:49.352 --> 29:50.701
Missing girl?

29:50.745 --> 29:54.096
He's gone.

29:54.140 --> 29:56.359
Paul Brown's gone?

29:56.403 --> 29:59.449
Left the county, state...

29:59.493 --> 30:02.583
country...Mexico...

30:02.626 --> 30:05.978
this morning when
your boy went missing.

30:06.021 --> 30:08.284
How do you know?

30:08.328 --> 30:10.678
I've been monitoring Paul.

30:10.721 --> 30:13.681
Can you put a warrant out?

30:13.724 --> 30:15.291
Not quite.

30:15.335 --> 30:19.687
I can almost make a case
but not quite.

30:19.730 --> 30:24.213
♪♪

30:24.257 --> 30:28.783
♪♪

30:28.827 --> 30:33.309
♪♪

30:33.353 --> 30:37.879
♪♪

30:37.923 --> 30:40.360
What's with the round-up?

30:40.403 --> 30:45.060
Sheriff: Those are the former
child-botherers.

30:45.104 --> 30:46.975
And?

30:47.019 --> 30:51.675
And there's
a missing child, Wesley...

30:51.719 --> 30:55.201
so holding and talking
to all of them.

30:55.244 --> 30:58.595
Well, David Lesser was with me
when that boy went missing,

30:58.639 --> 31:03.383
so if you don't mind,
let me run him home.

31:03.426 --> 31:08.649
♪♪

31:08.692 --> 31:10.912
Boy's missing?

31:10.956 --> 31:13.915
Yeah, pawn-shop kid.

31:13.959 --> 31:16.091
Glenn Pirdoo.

31:18.050 --> 31:21.227
Problematic dad...

31:21.270 --> 31:23.925
and maybe just run away.

31:25.361 --> 31:29.583
Paul's gone...as well?

31:29.626 --> 31:31.977
Yeah, Paul's gone.

31:34.501 --> 31:35.981
[ Sighs ]

31:36.024 --> 31:40.028
He's a dimwit, too,
I hear --

31:40.072 --> 31:42.944
the kid...

31:42.988 --> 31:46.905
with some minor to maybe
major brain damage.

31:48.689 --> 31:52.388
He might have just...
wandered off.

31:58.960 --> 32:01.832
Yeah, well...

32:01.876 --> 32:04.139
maybe not.

32:04.183 --> 32:06.272
What's that?

32:06.315 --> 32:08.927
Maybe not.

32:10.102 --> 32:12.713
Maybe
it's the worst thing.

32:12.756 --> 32:14.628
Wesley...

32:25.291 --> 32:28.816
...it's Father's Day,
Wesley...

32:28.859 --> 32:30.687
today.

32:33.952 --> 32:36.911
That's heartbreaking
for the dad.

32:38.217 --> 32:40.610
Problematic or not.

32:54.973 --> 32:56.104
[ Beep ]

32:56.148 --> 32:58.672
[ Ringing ]

32:58.715 --> 33:02.284
You've reached Richard Williams.
I'm unable to take your call.

33:02.328 --> 33:03.720
Please leave a message.

33:03.764 --> 33:06.680
Mr. Williams,
it's Wesley Walker.

33:06.723 --> 33:08.682
Hello.

33:08.725 --> 33:12.164
Um...

33:12.207 --> 33:14.209
I'm calling...

33:17.386 --> 33:20.824
...I don't have...an update,
exactly,

33:20.868 --> 33:24.393
about your daughter's case,
but I'm away from the office,

33:24.437 --> 33:27.266
following through on
an aspect of the case.

33:29.659 --> 33:33.315
I'm following through on
something, and...

33:33.359 --> 33:35.839
and I wanted you
to know that.

33:39.800 --> 33:41.889
Okay.

33:44.196 --> 33:47.199
Happy Father's Day,
as well.

33:47.242 --> 33:50.071
[ Sighs softly ]

33:50.115 --> 33:52.247
Okay.

33:52.291 --> 33:59.167
♪♪

33:59.211 --> 34:06.087
♪♪

34:06.131 --> 34:08.481
Paul's letters.

34:10.004 --> 34:11.875
Thanks.

34:11.919 --> 34:14.313
♪♪

34:14.356 --> 34:16.880
Now, they're not all
in there, Wesley.

34:16.924 --> 34:21.450
♪♪

34:21.494 --> 34:24.323
But there's quite a few.

34:24.366 --> 34:27.674
And you're welcome to it.

34:27.717 --> 34:29.937
Thanks, Dave.

34:29.980 --> 34:36.030
♪♪

34:36.074 --> 34:42.123
♪♪

34:42.167 --> 34:48.173
♪♪

34:48.216 --> 34:54.222
♪♪

34:54.266 --> 35:00.315
♪♪

35:00.359 --> 35:06.408
♪♪

35:06.452 --> 35:12.501
♪♪

35:12.545 --> 35:14.286
Woman:
This boy's disappeared?

35:14.329 --> 35:15.722
Yes, Judge.

35:15.765 --> 35:17.593
And Paul Allen Brown's
disappeared?

35:17.637 --> 35:19.508
Yes, Judge.

35:19.552 --> 35:21.162
And Paul Allen Brown
wrote

35:21.206 --> 35:23.512
that he would make
a little girl disappear?

35:23.556 --> 35:25.297
Yes, Judge.

35:25.340 --> 35:26.733
Okay, Wesley.

35:26.776 --> 35:30.040
You've got a warrant.
Arrest him.

35:33.131 --> 35:36.395
A little bit about me,
personally --

35:36.438 --> 35:40.573
I own a helicopter, and, yeah,
I'm a black belt in karate

35:40.616 --> 35:42.966
with red stripes
for some secret shit I know.

35:43.010 --> 35:45.447
Oh, pardon.

35:45.491 --> 35:47.014
You guys like video games?

35:47.057 --> 35:48.668
-Yeah.
-Yeah.

35:48.711 --> 35:53.368
I think video games
really hone

35:53.412 --> 35:55.283
a young man's hand-eye
coordination.

35:55.327 --> 35:58.243
At the end of the day,
I think they're awesome.

35:58.286 --> 36:01.115
I also believe the consumption
of pornography

36:01.159 --> 36:02.682
teaches boys intimacy.

36:02.725 --> 36:05.119
I foster its use.
I leave it lying around.

36:05.163 --> 36:09.819
♪♪

36:09.863 --> 36:14.520
♪♪

36:14.563 --> 36:19.264
♪♪

36:19.307 --> 36:24.007
♪♪

36:24.051 --> 36:28.708
♪♪

36:28.751 --> 36:33.191
And I won't be at work always,
like other dads.

36:33.234 --> 36:35.976
Sons, that's a promise.
That's a dad promise.

36:36.019 --> 36:40.415
But I will work enough
to enable me

36:40.459 --> 36:43.766
to surprise you
with gifts just 'cause.

36:43.810 --> 36:45.899
Just' cause.

36:47.422 --> 36:51.426
And I will always be there
for you -- always.

36:51.470 --> 36:53.950
When needed, when not.

36:53.994 --> 36:56.083
Hey, giving you space.

36:56.126 --> 36:58.259
You will have space.
You will have love.

36:58.303 --> 36:59.695
You will have girlfriends,

36:59.739 --> 37:02.263
as I shall teach you the ways.

37:02.307 --> 37:06.224
You'll be nourished by my care
and attention.

37:06.267 --> 37:08.574
We will make time for fun.

37:08.617 --> 37:11.620
You're the most important thing
in my life.

37:11.664 --> 37:13.274
You are number one.

37:13.318 --> 37:15.276
You're not alone.

37:15.320 --> 37:18.366
You are not...physically
unusual-looking.

37:18.410 --> 37:20.673
We come in all shapes and sizes.

37:20.716 --> 37:22.892
I love you.
I love you both.

37:22.936 --> 37:26.853
And I will fill your emptiness

37:26.896 --> 37:29.638
with wisdom and patience,

37:29.682 --> 37:33.512
and I will always be, sons,
the same...

37:33.555 --> 37:37.298
an open heart,
easy with a smile,

37:37.342 --> 37:41.998
quick to forgive, and just
the one to come to in a pinch,

37:42.042 --> 37:44.044
big or small.

37:44.087 --> 37:45.480
Dynamite!

37:45.524 --> 37:47.656
God, I love you.

37:47.700 --> 37:50.180
[ Children shouting playfully ]

37:57.536 --> 37:58.885
Hop in.

37:58.928 --> 38:01.627
Yep, that's right.
Follow the big one.

38:37.445 --> 38:40.274
[ Police radio chatter ]

38:47.542 --> 38:49.109
[ Beeping ]

39:28.714 --> 39:32.805
It's gonna be a long night
before the morning buzz.

39:32.848 --> 39:38.680
Glenn being gone might have
kicked up a hornets' nest.

39:38.724 --> 39:42.336
I hope we made
all the right moves.

39:42.380 --> 39:44.643
What you flashed me...

39:44.686 --> 39:46.427
Yeah?

39:46.471 --> 39:48.951
Two fingers.

39:51.476 --> 39:52.955
Yeah.

39:54.348 --> 39:56.306
Peace sign?

39:56.350 --> 39:59.701
'Cause it's too late
for peace...for me.

40:02.443 --> 40:05.403
No, it wasn't that.
It wasn't peace.

40:08.406 --> 40:09.929
How?

40:09.972 --> 40:13.280
I'm not like...

40:13.323 --> 40:15.674
probably not like you,
not directly.

40:16.979 --> 40:20.592
Yeah. I'm directly.

40:27.207 --> 40:29.514
The guy had 11 kids.

40:33.648 --> 40:35.911
[ Sighs ] Man.

40:35.955 --> 40:38.044
11.

40:38.087 --> 40:40.220
Fuck.

40:41.874 --> 40:43.919
11 kids just
wandering left now.

40:47.357 --> 40:52.145
What was your connection
if it wasn't direct?

40:54.103 --> 40:55.931
I ran away.

40:57.193 --> 41:00.458
Guy took my hose
and died in a fire.

41:03.417 --> 41:06.507
Well, maybe he should have
run away, too.

41:06.551 --> 41:09.336
Yeah, I say that
to myself a lot.

41:10.729 --> 41:12.513
Yeah, and?

41:14.123 --> 41:16.299
Now it doesn't do it.

41:16.343 --> 41:18.998
How did you get into
all of this, anyway?

41:19.041 --> 41:23.437
♪♪

41:23.481 --> 41:28.486
♪♪

41:28.529 --> 41:30.792
Have you found
a disillusioned young man

41:30.836 --> 41:33.534
to take your place there
in Half Whatever?

41:33.578 --> 41:34.666
Half Acre.

41:34.709 --> 41:37.277
Have you found someone?

41:37.320 --> 41:40.367
Someone disillusioned?

41:40.410 --> 41:45.328
Almost, but not, like,
disillusioned enough.

41:45.372 --> 41:48.070
♪♪

41:48.114 --> 41:50.725
[ Glass shatters ]

41:50.769 --> 41:55.904
♪♪

41:55.948 --> 42:01.823
♪♪

42:01.867 --> 42:04.696
Oh. Shit.

42:04.739 --> 42:06.741
I'm sorry.

42:10.092 --> 42:11.529
Oh.

42:11.572 --> 42:13.313
Man. Wow.

42:13.356 --> 42:16.534
Shit.

42:16.577 --> 42:18.840
I'm sorry.

42:18.884 --> 42:23.018
I was just coming in here to,
like, trade my car in

42:23.062 --> 42:28.589
for something,
um...less...

42:28.633 --> 42:33.420
so I could give the diff to a,
uh, colleague's,

42:33.463 --> 42:37.903
uh...offspring.

42:39.208 --> 42:41.167
And I gu-- I guess I just...

42:41.210 --> 42:44.213
lost my train of thought
there on the way in.

42:46.041 --> 42:48.087
I'm really sorry.

42:51.133 --> 42:55.660
Okay. Well...

42:55.703 --> 42:58.706
maybe I'll just leave
this here

